'''Astaga.com''' is an [[Indonesia]]n focused [[internet brand]] that was founded in 2000 as part of the Indonesian internet investment company Indonesia Online.<ref>[http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2000/04/13/astagacom-plans-listing-nasdaq.html "Astaga!com plans listing on Nasdaq" ''The Jakarta Post''] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219055445/http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2000/04/13/astagacom-plans-listing-nasdaq.html |date=December 19, 2013 }}, Jakarta | Business | April 13, 2000</ref> After investing US $7 million it was sold to [[South Africa]]n based [[Media conglomerate]], [[M-Web]] in 2001 for an undisclosed sum.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2001/01/17/mweb-acquires-100-stake-astagacom.html |title=M-Web acquires 100% stake in Astaga!com |work=thejakartapost.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219055821/http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2001/01/17/mweb-acquires-100-stake-astagacom.html |archivedate=2013-12-19 |df= }}</ref> It grew over the years and peaked in 2004 with over 300 employees and Indonesia wide presence. In late 2004 M-Web decided to exit Indonesia and sold the operating assets of Astaga.com and [[Kafegaul.com]] to a consortium of foreign and Indonesian investors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.thejakartapost.com/news/2002/11/16/mweb-indonesia-sells-assets-cut-jobs.html |title=M-WEB Indonesia sells assets, cut jobs |work=thejakartapost.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219180959/http://m.thejakartapost.com/news/2002/11/16/mweb-indonesia-sells-assets-cut-jobs.html |archivedate=2013-12-19 |df= }}</ref><ref>[http://cybertech.cbn.net.id/cbprtl/cybertech/detail.aspx?x=TechInfo&y=cybertech%7C0%7C0%7C2%7C2130 cybertech.cbn.net.id] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219053634/http://cybertech.cbn.net.id/cbprtl/cybertech/detail.aspx?x=TechInfo&y=cybertech%7C0%7C0%7C2%7C2130 |date=December 19, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.in