{{Infobox person |name = Ermirio Pereira de Moraes |image = |caption = | birth_name = Ermirio Pereira de Moraes Neto |birth_date = {{birth year and age|1952|06}} |birth_place = Brazil |death_date = |death_place = |other_names = |known_for = |occupation = Co-owner, [[Votorantim Group]] |education = |alma_mater = |nationality = Brazilian | residence = [[São Paulo]], Brazil | salary = | net_worth = $3.2 billion (December 2014)<ref name=Forbes/> | spouse = | children = 7 | parents = [[Antônio Ermírio de Moraes]] (father) | relatives = [[Maria Helena de Moraes]] (sister) }}
'''Ermirio Pereira de Moraes Neto''' (born June 1952) is a Brazilian businessman, co-owner of the privately held [[Votorantim Group]].
==Early life== Ermirio Pereira de Moraes was born in June 1952<ref name="companieshouse">{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/FC025377/officers|title=BANCO VOTORANTIM S.A. - Officers (free information from Companies House)|website=beta.companieshouse.gov.uk|accessdate=1 August 2017}}</ref> in Brazil, one of two children of the late [[Antônio Ermírio de Moraes]].<ref name=Forbes>{{cite web|title=Ermirio Pereira de Moraes|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/ermirio-pereira-de-moraes/|website=Forbes|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref> Moraes has a bachelor's degree in [[petroleum engineering]] from the [[University of Tulsa]] in [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]].<ref name=Forbes/>
==Career== Following the death of his father in 2014, he and his sister inherited control of [[Votorantim Group]], one of Brazil's largest privately held companies.<ref name=Forbes/>
According to ''Forbes'', he has an estimated net worth of $3.2&nbsp;billion in December 2014.<ref name=Forbes/>
==Personal life== He is married with seven children.<ref name=Forbes/>
