{{Infobox person |name=Michele Tiraboschi |birth_name= |image= |caption= |birth_date={{birth date and age|df=yes|1965|6|27}} |birth_place=[[Seriate, Bergamo]], Italy |nationality=Italian |alma_mater=University of Milano |occupation=Professor and writer |areas=Labour Law,Labour Market,industrial Relations,Youth Employment,Education and Employment }}
'''Michele Tiraboschi''' (born 27 June 1965 in [[Seriate]] – Italy) is a [[Full Professor]] of [[Labour Law]] at the [[University of Modena and Reggio Emilia]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Personal Page|url=http://personale.unimore.it/rubrica/dettaglio/tiraboschi|publisher=UNIMORE|accessdate=28 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Riforma del Lavoro, il punto del Professore Michele Tiraboschi|url=http://it.ibtimes.com/articles/28187/20120322/riforma-del-lavoro-il-punto-del-professore-michele-tiraboschi.htm|accessdate=28 November 2013|newspaper=International Business Times|date=22 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Tiraboschi (Adapt): "Stato e Regioni sono i primi ad abusare degli stage"|url=http://www.tempi.it/stage-tiraboschi-adapt-stato-regioni-abusi|accessdate=28 November 2013|newspaper=Tempi|date=24 August 2013}}</ref> Italy, and is the author of many [[publications]]. He is known for his participation in national debates on Italian [[labour market]] reforms and for his research in [[labour law]].<ref>{{cite web|title=S.Camusso e M.Tiraboschi: Monti e il Posto Fisso (Servizio Pubblico)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wBQbB1CLXlk|publisher=Il Fatto Quotidiano|accessdate=3 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Giorgiutti|first=Alessandro|title=Michele Tiraboschi: "La famosa 'flexicurity' ha fallito"|url=http://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/688489/Michele-Tiraboschi---La-famosa--flexcurity--ha-fallito-.html|accessdate=4 December 2013|newspaper=Libero Quotidiano|date=11/03/2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Michele Tiraboschi: vogliamo condizioni di lavoro decenti per i giovani|url=http://il-libero-professionista.confprofessioni.eu/2011/10/05/michele-tiraboschi-vogliamo-condizioni-di-lavoro-decenti-per-i-giovani/|accessdate=4 December 2013|newspaper=Il Libero Professionista|date=05/10/2011}}</ref>
== Professional career ==
Michele Tiraboschi is currently the Director of the [[Marco Biagi (jurist)|Marco Biagi]] Centre for International and Comparative Studies in [[Modena]] and the [[ADAPT – Association for International and Comparative Studies in Labour and Industrial relations]] in Bergamo.<ref>{{cite web|title=People|url=http://www.adapt.it/englishbulletin/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=88|publisher=ADAPT|accessdate=28 November 2013}}</ref> He is the founding editor of the [http://adapt.it/EJCLS/index.php/ejcls_adapt E-Journal of International and Comparative Labour Studies] and the Editor of the [http://www.adapt.it/englishbulletin/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=26 ADAPT Labour Studies Book-Series],<ref>{{cite web|title=ADAPT Labour Studies Book-Series |url=http://www.c-s-p.org/flyers/series_39.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130830142549/http://www.c-s-p.org/Flyers/series_39.htm |dead-url=yes |archive-date=30 August 2013 |publisher=Cambridge & Scholars Publishing |accessdate=28 November 2013 }}</ref> both are published by [http://www.adapt.it/adapt_university_press.html ADAPT University Press]. He is also the Deputy Director of the Italian Labour Law Review in Italian (Diritto delle Relazioni Industriali) (Giuffrè.).<ref>{{cite web|title=Diritto delle Relazioni Industriali|url=http://www.giuffre.it/it-it/products/21000013.html|publisher=Giuffrè|accessdate=28 November 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131230234717/http://www.giuffre.it/it-it/products/21000013.html|archivedate=30 December 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> From 2002 to 2008, Michele Tiraboschi was appointed by the President of the [[Italian Republic]] as a member of the Guarantee Committee for the implementation of the Law on [[the Right to Strike]]. He represented the [[Italian government]] in the Directorate of the [[European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working Conditions]]. For many years, he has been a consultant and legal advisor to the Italian Ministers of Labour and Social Policy, Higher Education and Research, and the Estonian Minister of Labour in the area of [[conflict of interest]].<ref>{{cite web|title=CV of Michele Tiraboschi|url=http://www.adapt.it/englishbulletin/docs/CV_Tiraboschi.pdf|publisher=ADAPT|accessdate=3 December 2013}}</ref>
== Publications ==
Professor Tiraboschi has published extensively in Italian and English in a wide range of areas in [[Labour Law]], [[labour market reform]]s, trade union law and community law, [[youth]] employment, education and employment, forms of representation of atypical/ temporary [[labour force]], and labour contracts.<ref>{{cite web|title=Michele Tiraboschi|url=https://www.google.com/search?q=Michele+Tiraboschi&btnG=Search+Books&tbm=bks&tbo=1|publisher=Google Books|accessdate=4 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Michele Tiraboschi's Publications|url=http://personale.unimore.it/rubrica/pubblicazioni/tiraboschi|publisher=University of Modena and Reggio Emilia|accessdate=4 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Michele Tiraboschi's Books|url=https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss/181-3781284-3562832?url=search-alias%3Dstripbooks&field-keywords=Michele+Tiraboschi|publisher=Amazon|accessdate=4 December 2013}}</ref> He is a columnist on employment and [[industrial relations]] of the Italian newspapers [[Il Sole 24 Ore]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Tiraboschi|first=Michele|title=ADAPTability – Lavoratori invisibili di un mercato del lavoro che cambia|url=http://marcominghetti.nova100.ilsole24ore.com/2013/11/adaptability-lavoratori-invisibili-di-un-mercato-del-lavoro-che-cambia.html|accessdate=29 November 2013|newspaper=Il Sole 24 Ore|date=27 November 2013}}</ref> and [[Avvenire]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Quaranta posti di dottorato di Adapt e Università di Bergamo|url=http://www.avvenire.it/Lavoro/Occupazione/Pagine/adapt-app.aspx|accessdate=29 November 2013|newspaper=Avvenire|date=30 October 2013}}</ref>
