{{Infobox person | name = Soegiarto Adikoesoemo | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth based on age as of date |80|2018|03|24}}<ref name="Forbes profile"/> | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = Surabaya, [[Jakarta]], Indonesia | nationality = Indonesian | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = businessman | known for = founder of [[AKR Corporindo]] | home_town = | salary = | networth = US$1.17 billion<ref name="Forbes profile">{{cite web|title=Forbes profile: Soegiarto Adikoesoemo|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/soegiarto-adikoesoemo/|website=Forbes|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref> | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | boards = | spouse = Married | children = 2, including [[Haryanto Adikoesoemo]] | parents = | relatives = | website = www.akr.co.id }} '''Soegiarto Adikoesoemo''' (born 1938) is an Indonesian [[billionaire]] businessman and the founder of [[AKR Corporindo]].
==Career== Soegiarto started a small chemical trading business in Surabaya and incorporated PT Aneka Kimia Raya in 1978, which traded and distributed basic chemicals in Indonesia.{{fact|date=March 2018}}
Soegiarto built Sorini a manufacturing plant for sorbitol in Indonesia and Khalista in China, and grew both plants to become one of the biggest producers in Asia.{{fact|date=March 2018}}
He is president commissioner of PT AKR Corporindo TBK.{{fact|date=March 2018}}
==Personal life== He is married, with two children, and lives in [[Surabaya]], [[Jakarta]], Indonesia.<ref name="Forbes profile"/>
His son [[Haryanto Adikoesoemo]] opened the [[Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art]] (Museum MACAN) in [[Kebun Jeruk]], a suburb of Jakarta, with 800 contemporary and modern art works from his collection.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/27/arts/design/jakarta-world-class-art-museum.html|title=Thanks to One Man’s Collection, Jakarta Now Has a World-Class Museum|first=Jon|last=Emont|date=27 November 2017|publisher=|accessdate=5 March 2018|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jenniferwang/2017/11/29/indonesias-richest-2017-heir-to-chemicals-fortune-brings-modern-art-to-indonesia/#39e392226873|title=Indonesia's Richest 2017: Heir To Chemicals Fortune Brings Modern Art To Indonesia|first=Jennifer|last=Wang|date=|website=forbes.com|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref>
